==Parser JavaScript para la generación de contenido==
<p class="pubdate">Fechas: <time>2012-09-20</time>

We are developing a JavaScript parser that will locally read all website content (in &quot;WikiReset&quot; format) and generate the corresponding static content to be served.

First of all, we are trying to make it parse correctly and recursively the WikiReset pages and generate the content for them. Then, we'll try to make it generate the templates files, per-page index menus, keyword listing... and who knows, maybe automatically detect words that could be links and create links out of them! :-D

----

==Getting rid of PHP (multilingual support)==
<p class="pubdate">Fechas: <time>2012-10-01</time>

This milestone is already finished. We have managed to make Apache take care of the language selection using content negotiation. The server loads a different HTML page that the parser should have already generated locally. We have also added URI rewritting rules and redirections to allow manual language modification by the user and to correctly display the selected language in the URI.

